  <main class="wrap">
    <!-- HOME -->
    <section id="home" class="section">
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h1>Teaching children to use sports equipment correctly</h1>
          <p class="muted">
            This simple, colourful, step-by-step manual helps learners practise safely, avoid injuries,
            and feel confident when using sports equipment during ball games and sports practice.
          </p>

          <div class="badgeRow" aria-label="Design specifications">
            <span class="badge accent">Simple language</span>
            <span class="badge purple">Short instructions</span>
            <span class="badge accent">Clear steps</span>
            <span class="badge purple">Diagrams (text-based)</span>
            <span class="badge">Lower-grade friendly</span>
          </div>

          <div class="rule" style="margin-top:14px;">
            <strong>Problem:</strong> Many learners struggle to use basic ball game equipment correctly, which can lead to injuries during sports practices.
          </div>

          <div class="rule purple">
            <strong>Intent:</strong> Teach learners the proper use of sports equipment so they can follow instructions easily and become more confident during sports activities.
          </div>

          <div class="rule warn">
            <strong>Safety first:</strong> If equipment is broken, wet, sharp, or unsafe, stop and tell the teacher immediately.
          </div>

          <p class="mini muted">
            Tip: Use the menu at the top to jump to sections. You can also press <span class="kbd">Ctrl</span> + <span class="kbd">F</span> and search “cones”, “whistle”, or “shin guards”.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h2>Quick Rules (Read before playing)</h2>
          <ol class="list">
            <li><strong>Listen</strong> to the teacher’s instructions first.</li>
            <li><strong>Check</strong> the area: no stones, glass, or holes.</li>
            <li><strong>Wear</strong> correct gear: shoes tied, shin guards for soccer, no jewellery.</li>
            <li><strong>Use</strong> equipment for its purpose (cones are not hats, whistles are not toys).</li>
            <li><strong>Stop</strong> if someone is hurt and call the teacher.</li>
          </ol>

          <div class="controls">
            <button type="button" onclick="window.location.href='#manual'">Start the Manual</button>
            <button class="secondary" type="button" onclick="window.print()">Print this page</button>
          </div>

          <p class="mini muted" style="margin-top:10px;">
            Printing makes it work like a booklet/manual (Stage 4 improvement: bold headings + colourful pages).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MANUAL -->
    <section id="manual" class="section">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Step-by-Step Instruction Manual</h2>
        <p class="muted">
          Follow these steps every time you do ball games or sports practice.
          The steps are short and easy to remember.
        </p>

        <div class="two" style="margin-top:12px;">
          <div class="card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,.03); box-shadow:none;">
            <h3>Step 1: Get ready</h3>
            <ol class="steps">
              <li>Remove jewellery (rings, earrings, chains).</li>
              <li>Tie shoelaces properly.</li>
              <li>Wear the correct gear (example: shin guards for soccer).</li>
              <li>Warm up (light jogging + stretching).</li>
            </ol>
            <div class="doDont">
              <div class="box good">
                <strong>DO</strong>
                <ul class="list">
                  <li>Ask if you are unsure.</li>
                  <li>Keep water nearby.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="box bad">
                <strong>DON’T</strong>
                <ul class="list">
                  <li>Play with untied shoes.</li>
                  <li>Push or trip others.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,.03); box-shadow:none;">
            <h3>Step 2: Check the equipment</h3>
            <ol class="steps">
              <li>Look for cracks, sharp edges, or broken parts.</li>
              <li>Check if the ground is slippery or wet.</li>
              <li>Make sure cones and markers are visible.</li>
              <li>Tell the teacher if something is unsafe.</li>
            </ol>
            <div class="rule">
              <strong>Remember:</strong> Safe equipment = safe practice.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="two" style="margin-top:14px;">
          <div class="card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,.03); box-shadow:none;">
            <h3>Step 3: Use equipment correctly</h3>
            <ol class="steps">
              <li>Use equipment only for the game (no throwing cones, no swinging sticks).</li>
              <li>Wait your turn in drills.</li>
              <li>Keep a safe distance when someone is kicking or throwing.</li>
              <li>Follow the teacher’s whistle or signal.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <div class="card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,.03); box-shadow:none;">
            <h3>Step 4: Pack away safely</h3>
            <ol class="steps">
              <li>Carry equipment carefully (do not drag goal posts or nets).</li>
              <li>Stack cones neatly.</li>
              <li>Return bibs/vests and count them.</li>
              <li>Wash hands after practice.</li>
            </ol>
            <div class="rule purple">
              <strong>Good habit:</strong> Packing away properly keeps equipment in good condition and prevents accidents.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- EQUIPMENT (NOT ONLY BALLS) -->
    <section id="equipment" class="section">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Equipment Guide (Ball Games)</h2>
        <p class="muted">
          This section explains equipment used <strong>around</strong> ball games (not only the ball).
          Each item has short instructions and safety tips.
        </p>

        <div class="three" style="margin-top:12px;">
          <!-- Soccer -->
          <div class="equip">
            <div class="equipHead">
              <div>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 4px;">Soccer (Football)</h3>
                <div class="mini muted">Equipment used around the game</div>
              </div>
              <span class="tag safe">Safe Play</span>
            </div>

            <div class="rule">
              <strong>Main safety idea:</strong> Protect legs and keep the field clear.
            </div>

            <ul class="list">
              <li><strong>Shin guards:</strong> Wear under socks. They protect your shins from kicks.</li>
              <li><strong>Cones/markers:</strong> Used for dribbling lanes and boundaries. Do not kick them.</li>
              <li><strong>Goal posts & net:</strong> Do not hang on the net or climb the posts.</li>
              <li><strong>Bibs/vests:</strong> Wear to show teams. Return them after the game.</li>
              <li><strong>Whistle:</strong> Only the teacher uses it. Stop when you hear it.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="doDont">
              <div class="box good">
                <strong>DO</strong>
                <ul class="list">
                  <li>Keep space when someone shoots.</li>
                  <li>Check for holes on the field.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="box bad">
                <strong>DON’T</strong>
                <ul class="list">
                  <li>Slide tackle on hard ground.</li>
                  <li>Play without shin guards.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Netball -->
          <div class="equip">
            <div class="equipHead">
              <div>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 4px;">Netball</h3>
                <div class="mini muted">Equipment used around the game</div>
              </div>
              <span class="tag care">Careful</span>
            </div>

            <div class="rule purple">
              <strong>Main safety idea:</strong> Safe passing and safe landing.
            </div>

            <ul class="list">
              <li><strong>Netball bibs:</strong> Show positions (GS, GA, etc.). Do not swap without permission.</li>
              <li><strong>Netball post & ring:</strong> Do not pull or swing on the post.</li>
              <li><strong>Boundary lines/markers:</strong> Stay inside the court to avoid collisions.</li>
              <li><strong>Cones:</strong> Used for footwork drills. Step around them, don’t jump on them.</li>
              <li><strong>Stopwatch/whistle:</strong> Teacher controls time and stops play.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="doDont">
              <div class="box good">
                <strong>DO</strong>
                <ul class="list">
                  <li>Land with knees slightly bent.</li>
                  <li>Pass with two hands.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="box bad">
                <strong>DON’T</strong>
                <ul class="list">
                  <li>Push when defending.</li>
                  <li>Run into the post area.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Basketball -->
          <div class="equip">
            <div class="equipHead">
              <div>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 4px;">Basketball</h3>
                <div class="mini muted">Equipment used around the game</div>
              </div>
              <span class="tag safe">Safe Play</span>
            </div>

            <div class="rule">
              <strong>Main safety idea:</strong> Keep hands safe and avoid collisions.
            </div>

            <ul class="list">
              <li><strong>Hoop & backboard:</strong> Do not hang on the rim.</li>
              <li><strong>Court lines:</strong> Follow boundaries to prevent running into others.</li>
              <li><strong>Cones:</strong> Used for dribbling drills. Keep your head up while dribbling.</li>
              <li><strong>Whistle:</strong> Stop immediately when you hear it.</li>
              <li><strong>Scoreboard/clipboard:</strong> Teacher uses it; learners should not fight over it.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="doDont">
              <div class="box good">
                <strong>DO</strong>
                <ul class="list">
                  <li>Call “mine” when catching.</li>
                  <li>Keep nails short.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="box bad">
                <strong>DON’T</strong>
                <ul class="list">
                  <li>Push during rebounds.</li>
                  <li>Run under someone jumping.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="two" style="margin-top:14px;">
          <div class="equip">
            <div class="equipHead">
              <div>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 4px;">General Equipment (Any Ball Game)</h3>
                <div class="mini muted">Used in many sports practices</div>
              </div>
              <span class="tag care">Careful</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="list">
              <li><strong>Cones:</strong> Place them flat. Keep them away from running lanes if not used.</li>
              <li><strong>Skipping ropes:</strong> Use enough space. Do not swing near faces.</li>
              <li><strong>First-aid kit:</strong> Teacher keeps it. Report injuries quickly.</li>
              <li><strong>Water bottle:</strong> Drink water during breaks to avoid dehydration.</li>
              <li><strong>Storage bag/box:</strong> Pack equipment neatly to prevent damage.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="equip">
            <div class="equipHead">
              <div>
                <h3 style="margin:0 0 4px;">Improvised Demonstration Tools (If equipment is limited)</h3>
                <div class="mini muted">Creative + recycling idea</div>
              </div>
              <span class="tag safe">Safe Play</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="list">
              <li><strong>Cones:</strong> Recycled bottles filled with a little sand (stable).</li>
              <li><strong>Markers:</strong> Old cloth strips or chalk lines.</li>
              <li><strong>Soft practice ball:</strong> Rolled plastic bags wrapped with tape (for gentle drills only).</li>
              <li><strong>Rope:</strong> Old fabric braided into a line for boundaries.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="rule warn">
              <strong>Important:</strong> Improvised tools must be checked for sharp edges and must be safe for children.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- QUIZ -->
    <section id="quiz" class="section">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Quick Safety Quiz</h2>
        <p class="muted">Answer these questions to check if you understand how to use equipment safely.</p>

        <div id="quizBox">
          <div class="quizQ" data-answer="B">
            <div class="prompt">1) In soccer, what equipment protects your legs?</div>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s1" value="A"> A whistle</label>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s1" value="B"> Shin guards</label>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s1" value="C"> A cone</label>
          </div>

          <div class="quizQ" data-answer="A">
            <div class="prompt">2) What should you do if a cone is broken and sharp?</div>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s2" value="A"> Stop and tell the teacher</label>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s2" value="B"> Keep playing and ignore it</label>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s2" value="C"> Throw it away yourself</label>
          </div>

          <div class="quizQ" data-answer="C">
            <div class="prompt">3) Who should use the whistle during practice?</div>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s3" value="A"> Any learner</label>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s3" value="B"> The team captain only</label>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s3" value="C"> The teacher/coach</label>
          </div>

          <div class="quizQ" data-answer="B">
            <div class="prompt">4) What is the safest way to pack away cones?</div>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s4" value="A"> Kick them into a pile</label>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s4" value="B"> Stack them neatly and carry them</label>
            <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="s4" value="C"> Leave them on the field</label>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="controls">
          <button type="button" onclick="checkSafetyQuiz()">Check Score</button>
          <button class="secondary" type="button" onclick="resetSafetyQuiz()">Reset</button>
          <div id="quizResult" class="result" aria-live="polite">Score: —</div>
        </div>

        <div class="rule purple" style="margin-top:12px;">
          <strong>Recommendation:</strong> Add more information and demonstrations, and make it more colourful (this page is designed to be colourful and easy to read).
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

